<i>adverb</i>: 친절히 [친절히], 살뜰히 [살뜰히], 부디 [부ː디], 따뜻이 [따뜨시] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>adverb</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>친절히 [친절히]</dt><br>
<dd>kindly; nicely</dd><br>
<dd>사람을 대하는 태도가 상냥하고 부드럽게.</dd><br>
<dd>With an attitude that is gentle and soft, when treating someone.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>살뜰히 [살뜰히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. sincerely; kindly</dd><br>
<dd>마음이나 행동이 정성스럽고 친절하며 다정하게.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing one thinking or acting sincerely, kindly and affectionately.</dd><br>
<dd>2. meticulously; frugally</dd><br>
<dd>일이나 살림을 착실하고 실속 있게 하여 빈틈이 없게.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing one doing a job or house chores dutifully and thoroughly, without wasting resources.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>부디 [부ː디]</dt><br>
<dd>please; kindly</dd><br>
<dd>간절하게 바라건대. 또는 될 수 있는 대로.</dd><br>
<dd>I hope eagerly; if possible.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>따뜻이 [따뜨시]</dt><br>
<dd>1. warm; warmly</dd><br>
<dd>아주 덥지 않고 기분 좋은 정도로 알맞게 높은 온도로.</dd><br>
<dd>In an appropriately high temperature that is pleasing, not too hot.</dd><br>
<dd>2. warmly; kindly</dd><br>
<dd>마음, 감정, 태도, 분위기 등이 정답고 편안하게.</dd><br>
<dd>With an affectionate and comfortable state of mind, feeling, attitude, atmosphere, etc.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>